  "case_summary": "Patent exhaustion does not permit a farmer to reproduce patent- ed seeds through planting and harvesting without the patent holder’s permission. (a) Under the patent exhaustion doctrine, “the initial authorized sale of a patented article terminates all patent rights to that item,” Quanta Computer, Inc. v. LG Electronics, Inc., 553 U. S. 617, 625, and confers on the purchaser, or any subsequent owner, “the right to use [or] sell” the thing as he sees fit, United States v. Univis Lens Co.,",
